10:33.299 --> 10:35.232
both: Ipsy-tipsy, go!

10:35.301 --> 10:36.400
- Wait, hold on. Claire?

10:36.469 --> 10:38.069
Claire!
- Yeah?

10:38.138 --> 10:40.137
- Hey. Do you wanna
come in here with us?

10:40.206 --> 10:42.640
- I actually just opened
a bottle of red if you wanna...

10:42.709 --> 10:44.008
- I'll take a beer.
- Well, they're in the fridge.

10:44.077 --> 10:45.543
- Sorry, babe.
- Yeah, w-we're playing.

10:45.612 --> 10:47.411
Sorry, babe.
<i>- Wha-ah! You little--</i>

10:47.480 --> 10:48.512
<i>- [laughs]</i>

10:48.581 --> 10:50.214
You're hitting somebody else.

10:50.283 --> 10:51.649
- Oh!
How'd you get a--

10:51.718 --> 10:53.384
Hey.
- Hi.

10:53.453 --> 10:54.752
[grunts]

10:54.821 --> 10:56.287
- Hey, you know what?
Actually, let me just--

10:56.356 --> 10:57.922
Would you mind--
Yeah, that's better.

10:57.991 --> 10:59.423
Just--thanks.
- There you go.

10:59.492 --> 11:01.792
- Yeah, Sue, I got your email.

11:01.861 --> 11:03.227
[both laughing]
- I got you!

11:03.296 --> 11:05.863
- Yeah. No, I-I-I got the email.

11:05.932 --> 11:07.398
- Totally ready for sex
whenever you want.

11:07.467 --> 11:09.034
You just let me know.
- We love you.

11:10.870 --> 11:13.571
Claire, you want to do
the taste test?

11:13.640 --> 11:15.039
- Ugh.
- Come on, Claire.

11:15.108 --> 11:16.841
This is for you.
It's about your needs.

11:16.910 --> 11:19.110
- Brad, I actually think
you should go home.

11:19.179 --> 11:20.244
<i>[somber piano music]</i>

11:20.313 --> 11:21.579
- This is his home.

11:21.648 --> 11:23.380
- Well, I'd like
my house back,

11:23.449 --> 11:25.416
so if you guys
are gonna hang out,

11:25.485 --> 11:26.817
I guess I'm gonna go
sleep on the couch.

11:26.886 --> 11:29.053
<i>[quirky music]</i>
- [grunting]

11:29.122 --> 11:30.155
- We'll see you there.

11:34.360 --> 11:35.993
<i>- The new</i>
<i>Plains-Evergreen line,</i>

11:36.062 --> 11:37.862
<i>from Minnesota</i>
<i>to the West Coast.</i>

11:37.931 --> 11:40.564
<i>Experience the beauty</i>
<i>of America.</i>

11:40.633 --> 11:43.467
- Come see us in Minnesota!

11:43.536 --> 11:45.169
<i>- In North Dakota!</i>

11:45.238 --> 11:47.037
<i>- Montana!</i>

11:47.106 --> 11:48.506
<i>- Idaho!</i>

11:48.575 --> 11:49.974
- And this is where I come in.
Oregon.

11:50.043 --> 11:51.709
We got passed by last year
because it went

11:51.778 --> 11:53.911
straight through Washington
into Seattle.

11:53.980 --> 11:55.012
Not this year.

11:55.081 --> 11:56.714
Isn't this exciting?
- Very exciting.

11:56.783 --> 11:59.183
And how are we going
to shoot this, sir?

11:59.252 --> 12:00.751
- Helicopter, Sam.

12:00.820 --> 12:01.719
Like this one.

12:01.788 --> 12:03.220
Got a camera on the front.

12:03.289 --> 12:04.321
<i>[siren wailing]</i>

12:04.390 --> 12:06.490
[imitates helicopter zooming]

12:06.559 --> 12:09.226
- I-I think this is
the right spot.

12:09.295 --> 12:10.795
- Seems like the right spot.

12:10.864 --> 12:12.663
I mean, we're at the highest
point on the hill, right?

12:12.732 --> 12:14.598
- Yeah.
- And we'll--we'll certainly

12:14.667 --> 12:16.066
hear the helicopter
before it arrives,

12:16.135 --> 12:18.435
and we--we probably will see it.

12:18.504 --> 12:21.072
[wind whooshing]

12:24.377 --> 12:26.243
And Oregon!

12:26.312 --> 12:30.080
[echoing] And Oregon!
And Oregon! And Oregon!

12:30.149 --> 12:32.449
[wind whooshing]

12:32.518 --> 12:36.086
You don't think it's
"Or Oregon," do you?

12:36.155 --> 12:37.488
- Hmm.

12:37.557 --> 12:38.689
- Or Oregon!

12:38.758 --> 12:40.024
[echoing]
Or Oregon! Or Oregon!

12:40.093 --> 12:41.325
And Oregon!

12:41.394 --> 12:42.459
[echoing] And Oregon!
And Oregon!

12:42.528 --> 12:43.694
Or Oregon!

12:43.763 --> 12:44.995
[echoing] Or Oregon!
Or Oregon!

12:45.064 --> 12:46.864
I think "And Oregon"
sounds better,

12:46.933 --> 12:50.701
but I think "Or Oregon"
is more grammatically correct.

12:50.770 --> 12:53.437
But "Or Oregon"
sounds very strange.

12:53.506 --> 12:54.738
And Oregon!
[echoing] And Oregon!

12:54.807 --> 12:56.006
That--see, that makes
more sense.

12:56.075 --> 12:57.174
That feels
more comfortable to me

12:57.243 --> 12:58.676
to go, "And Oregon!"

12:58.745 --> 13:01.011
[echoing] And Oregon!
And Oregon! And Oregon!

13:01.080 --> 13:04.181
[wind whooshing]

13:04.250 --> 13:06.518
Sam, you can't be here
when it comes over.

13:07.720 --> 13:08.853
It's only supposed to be me.

13:08.922 --> 13:10.554
- Oh.
- But I need you up here.

13:10.623 --> 13:12.456
- Okay.
- So maybe

13:12.525 --> 13:14.992
you can gather some weeds and
turn yourself into a shrubbery,

13:15.061 --> 13:17.761
and then when it flies over,
you're just gonna crouch down

13:17.830 --> 13:20.197
and you become
like a little bush.

13:20.266 --> 13:23.500
[wind whooshing]

13:23.569 --> 13:25.703
And we're still close enough.
I think we'll--

13:25.772 --> 13:27.972
If we hear anything...

13:28.041 --> 13:29.306
we'll be okay.

13:29.375 --> 13:32.276
[wind whooshing]

13:32.345 --> 13:33.911
[helicopter rotors whirring]

13:33.980 --> 13:36.146
[inhales sharply]
Sam, hurry!

13:36.215 --> 13:38.315
And Oregon!
And Oregon!

13:38.384 --> 13:39.717
And Oregon! Or Oregon!

13:39.786 --> 13:41.952
Or Oregon! And Oregon!

13:42.021 --> 13:43.821
And Oregon!

13:43.890 --> 13:47.458
Oh, shoot.

13:47.527 --> 13:49.560
- Eh, wrong helicopter.

13:49.629 --> 13:52.630
- Yeah. Wonder what they're
doing way out here.

13:55.702 --> 13:57.401
Well, that was a good
trial run.

13:57.470 --> 14:00.438
[wind whooshing]

14:02.909 --> 14:04.675
I had a weird thing
the other day.

14:04.744 --> 14:06.977
Remember that--those journalists
that came in,

14:07.046 --> 14:09.079
the photojournalists,
wanted to do a big story?

14:09.148 --> 14:10.547
- Yeah.

14:10.616 --> 14:12.583
- You know, they--
there were a lot of them

14:12.652 --> 14:13.918
for just a photo shoot.

14:13.987 --> 14:15.486
It was, like,
ten people there.

14:15.555 --> 14:17.221
And it's just me, you know,

14:17.290 --> 14:19.723
and they took a few pictures,
and--which was nice.

14:19.792 --> 14:21.859
And then they all, like,
got really happy.

14:21.928 --> 14:24.094
And they were all clapping,
right?

14:24.163 --> 14:25.763
And they were like,
"Congratulations!"

14:25.832 --> 14:27.464
And they were all
high-fiving each other

14:27.533 --> 14:29.400
and back-slapping,
and I was like,

14:29.469 --> 14:31.669
"It's just a few pictures."

14:31.738 --> 14:32.870
- Yeah.
- Yeah, I don't--

14:32.939 --> 14:34.706
I didn't really
understand that.

14:38.578 --> 14:40.878
<i>- The new</i>
<i>Plains-Evergreen line.</i>

14:40.947 --> 14:43.380
<i>Experience the beauty</i>
<i>of America.</i>

14:43.449 --> 14:46.116
- Come see us in Minnesota!

14:46.185 --> 14:47.818
- In North Dakota!

14:47.887 --> 14:49.487
- Montana!

14:49.555 --> 14:51.789
<i>- And/or anywhere</i>
<i>in the Pacific Northwest.</i>

14:51.858 --> 14:55.093
[helicopter rotors whirring]

14:59.232 --> 15:03.200
<i>[upbeat rock music]</i>

15:03.269 --> 15:05.703
[bird calling]

15:05.772 --> 15:07.771
- Oh, this is really nice.

15:07.840 --> 15:09.239
- Hey there.
Keep an eye out.

15:09.308 --> 15:11.041
There's a barred owl
up there.

15:11.110 --> 15:12.042
- Okay.
- Cool.

15:12.111 --> 15:13.677
Thanks.
- Thanks.

15:13.746 --> 15:16.381
[bird calling]
I don't see anything.

15:17.116 --> 15:18.449
- Where'd he say it was?

15:18.518 --> 15:19.450
[crunches]

15:19.519 --> 15:21.151
- Oh, no!

15:21.220 --> 15:23.020
No! No, no, no, no!

15:23.089 --> 15:24.388
- Oh-ho!

15:24.457 --> 15:26.156
Fred, it's--it's okay.

15:26.225 --> 15:27.324
- It's not okay.

15:27.393 --> 15:29.326
I killed a snail.

15:29.395 --> 15:30.794
Such a delicate little shell,

15:30.863 --> 15:32.930
and I just stomped on it
like a Frankenstein.

15:32.999 --> 15:34.165
- Come on.

15:34.234 --> 15:35.866
- H-he was just minding
his own business.

15:35.935 --> 15:37.868
I need to do
some soul-searching.

15:37.937 --> 15:40.471
I'm just gonna just walk
for a little while.

15:40.540 --> 15:42.840
- Okay.
- [sighs]

15:42.909 --> 15:45.009
- [sighs]

15:45.078 --> 15:48.012
<i>[somber music]</i>

15:48.081 --> 15:50.214
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:50.283 --> 15:53.917
[faint childlike laughter]

15:53.986 --> 15:56.987
<i>[light music]</i>

15:57.056 --> 15:59.891
[laughter continues]

16:00.460 --> 16:02.159
- Wow.

16:02.228 --> 16:03.327
Hello?

16:03.396 --> 16:04.695
- Aah!
- Ow, my ears hurt.

16:04.764 --> 16:06.497
You're talking really loud.

16:06.566 --> 16:08.265
- Hi, um...

16:08.334 --> 16:09.266
I'm a human.

16:09.335 --> 16:10.367
- You're still yelling.

16:10.436 --> 16:12.169
- Is this a better volume?

16:12.238 --> 16:13.270
- It's fine.

16:13.339 --> 16:14.371
- Who are you?

16:14.440 --> 16:15.672
- Um...

16:15.741 --> 16:17.908
as you can tell, I'm--
I'm a human being,

16:17.977 --> 16:21.178
and I-I was just walking
through the forest,

16:21.247 --> 16:22.212
and I have something
to tell you.

16:22.281 --> 16:23.380
Can you guys all hear me?

16:23.449 --> 16:25.416
- Ooh, gossip. We love gossip.

16:25.485 --> 16:26.950
- It's not gossip.

16:27.019 --> 16:29.920
Uh, it's--it's something
a little more urgent.

16:29.989 --> 16:33.457
- We want gossip.
- Yeah! Tell us your gossip.

16:33.526 --> 16:34.792
- I-I'll think
of some gossip for you.

16:34.861 --> 16:37.561
Th-this is a little more
on the serious side.

16:37.630 --> 16:39.329
- Fine.
- Okay?

16:39.398 --> 16:43.801
So...I was walking around
back there,

16:43.870 --> 16:45.736
and I'm bigger than you guys,

16:45.805 --> 16:47.404
and, you know, you--
you camouflage

16:47.473 --> 16:49.006
pretty well into the ground.

16:49.075 --> 16:50.340
It's not your fault.

16:50.409 --> 16:53.010
And...I wasn't looking down,

16:53.079 --> 16:56.014
and I--and I stepped
on one of you guys.

16:57.550 --> 17:01.152
- S-so is the snail dead?

17:02.488 --> 17:04.188
- I believe so.
- [gasps]

17:04.257 --> 17:06.356
- And I am so sorry.

17:06.425 --> 17:08.157
I feel horrible.

17:08.227 --> 17:09.726
- That's not a problem.

17:09.795 --> 17:11.862
- Being a snail sucks.
We want to die.

17:11.931 --> 17:13.597
- What?
- Look at us.

17:13.665 --> 17:16.400
We're made of slime.
- People think we're gross.

17:16.469 --> 17:17.634
- I do notice
that it's a very s--

17:17.703 --> 17:18.801
you guys go really slow.

17:18.871 --> 17:20.204
I mean, that must be
frustrating.

17:20.272 --> 17:22.973
- A snail's pace.
Ever heard of it?

17:23.041 --> 17:24.074
- That's you guys.

17:24.143 --> 17:25.108
- Yeah, a snail's pace.

17:25.178 --> 17:27.944
- We're the worst animal.

17:28.013 --> 17:29.246
Can you do us a favor?

17:29.315 --> 17:31.181
- Sure.

17:31.250 --> 17:32.683
- Could you kill us?
- No.

17:32.752 --> 17:33.984
It's gonna make me
feel terrible.

17:34.053 --> 17:35.786
- Come on.
All snails want to die.

17:35.855 --> 17:37.554
- Yeah!
Could you kill us?

17:37.623 --> 17:38.689
- You want to die?

17:38.758 --> 17:39.923
- Do it!
- Step on us.

17:39.992 --> 17:41.191
- Just kill us.
- It'll feel fine

17:41.260 --> 17:43.827
'cause we'll feel fine.

17:43.896 --> 17:45.129
- I'll do one.

17:45.198 --> 17:46.196
- Yes!
- Kill us.

17:46.265 --> 17:47.764
We want that sweet release.

17:47.833 --> 17:48.899
- Me too!

17:48.967 --> 17:50.134
- Maybe I'll do two.
- That's great!

17:50.203 --> 17:51.301
- Great!
- Step on us.

17:51.370 --> 17:52.636
- Do it.
- Stop wasting time.

17:52.705 --> 17:53.737
- Do it now.
- All right, everybody,

17:53.806 --> 17:54.872
calm down.
- Do it now!

17:54.941 --> 17:56.240
- Calm down.
- Stomp on me!

17:56.309 --> 17:57.441
- All right.
- Kill us.

17:57.510 --> 17:58.475
- Please, now!
- Kill us!

17:58.544 --> 17:59.476
- Do it!
- Step on me.

17:59.545 --> 18:00.844
- Kill us!

18:00.913 --> 18:01.645
[crunches]

18:01.714 --> 18:02.746
Yeah!
- You...

18:02.815 --> 18:03.981
[crunches]
- Thank you.

18:04.050 --> 18:05.082
- And you.
- See ya!

18:05.151 --> 18:06.450
[crunches]

18:06.519 --> 18:08.552
- [sighs]

18:08.621 --> 18:10.721
<i>I feel much better now.</i>

18:10.790 --> 18:12.789
- Good, I was, uh,
really worried about you.

18:12.858 --> 18:14.658
- Aw.
<i>- Et voilà.</i>

18:14.727 --> 18:16.593
<i>Escargot</i> for <i> monsieur</i>
and for <i> madame.</i>

18:16.662 --> 18:19.062
<i>- Merci beaucoup.</i>
<i>- Bon appétit.</i>

18:19.131 --> 18:20.330
- All right, let's dig in.

18:20.399 --> 18:24.368
<i>[laughter echoing]</i>

18:24.437 --> 18:25.837
<i>- Bye-bye!</i>

18:35.114 --> 18:37.748
- Brad, you're not gonna
believe this. [laughs]

18:39.418 --> 18:41.785
What happened?
Are you crying?

18:41.854 --> 18:44.288
- [inhales raggedly]
Ask her.

18:44.357 --> 18:45.589
- Doug...

18:45.658 --> 18:48.592
I'm ending things with Brad.

18:48.661 --> 18:51.728
- What? You can't do that.
No!

18:51.797 --> 18:54.031
Claire, get him a Kleenex
or something.

18:54.100 --> 18:57.034
<i>[dramatic string music]</i>

18:57.103 --> 19:02.339
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:02.408 --> 19:03.707
I don't understand.

19:03.776 --> 19:06.043
We were having
such a great time, and...

19:06.112 --> 19:09.279
what happened to the whole
open relationship thing?

19:09.348 --> 19:11.381
- I'm not happy.

19:11.450 --> 19:14.618
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:14.687 --> 19:17.154
- No, that's [bleep] up.

19:17.223 --> 19:21.158
I mean...Brad, it's not you.

19:21.227 --> 19:22.793
It's her.

19:22.862 --> 19:24.962
- Thanks for saying that, Doug.

19:25.031 --> 19:26.363
Means a lot to me.

19:26.432 --> 19:27.831
- No, it is him.

19:27.900 --> 19:29.499
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:29.568 --> 19:33.170
- It's one of you
and...one of me.

19:33.239 --> 19:35.038
- No.

19:35.107 --> 19:37.507
I mean, it's definitely not me.

19:37.576 --> 19:39.876
- [sobbing]

19:39.945 --> 19:42.413
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:48.020 --> 19:52.956
Hey, I-I-I don't have
anything to fidget with.

19:53.025 --> 19:55.059
[chair creaking]

19:56.462 --> 19:59.396
Thank you.

19:59.465 --> 20:01.164
- Could we turn on
a light or something?

20:01.233 --> 20:02.766
It's really dark.

20:02.835 --> 20:03.634
- No.

20:03.703 --> 20:05.970
It's--it's a breakup.

20:06.906 --> 20:09.806
<i>- Can I speak?</i>
<i>Can I say something?</i>

20:09.875 --> 20:11.141
- Do you hear yourself
right now?

20:11.210 --> 20:12.142
Do you hear yourself?

20:12.211 --> 20:13.443
- I loved you both!

20:13.512 --> 20:14.711
- Those aren't my words.

20:14.780 --> 20:16.546
- No, of course I remember that.
[laughs]

20:16.615 --> 20:19.149
- [laughs]
<i>- Hey, Doug, this is Brad</i>

20:19.218 --> 20:20.784
<i>who I've been</i>
<i>telling you about.</i>

20:20.853 --> 20:22.486
<i>- It's not really work</i>
<i>if you enjoy it.</i>

20:22.555 --> 20:23.487
<i>[echoing] Not really work</i>
<i>if you enjoy it.</i>

20:23.556 --> 20:24.655
- I'm just invisible.

20:24.724 --> 20:26.023
- I loved you both.

20:26.092 --> 20:27.524
<i>Come on, Claire.</i>
<i>This is for you.</i>

20:27.593 --> 20:29.092
- Wow, I never thought of it
that way.

20:29.161 --> 20:30.827
<i>- Doug, I'd like to have</i>
<i>an open relationship.</i>

20:30.896 --> 20:32.129
<i>[echoing] To have</i>
<i>an open relationship.</i>

20:32.198 --> 20:33.630
I'm sorry.
- I'm sorry.

20:33.699 --> 20:34.998
- [sobbing]
- You know what?

20:35.067 --> 20:36.199
You're not listening.

20:36.268 --> 20:37.401
[crying]
<i>- It's about your needs.</i>

20:37.470 --> 20:38.936
<i>- I didn't get a kiss emoji.</i>

20:39.005 --> 20:41.572
<i>- Brad, I actually think</i>
<i>you should go home.</i>

20:43.275 --> 20:45.208
- I can't see anything.

20:45.277 --> 20:47.378
Will you please
turn on a light?

20:48.414 --> 20:49.914
- Fine.

20:51.484 --> 20:53.083
<i>[tense music]</i>
- Hey, guys.

20:53.152 --> 20:55.453
- Jesus.

20:56.188 --> 20:57.888
- I'm Shannon.

20:58.958 --> 21:00.524
I'm your fourth?

21:00.593 --> 21:03.093
- You didn't park in my spot
by any chance, did you?

21:03.162 --> 21:04.194
- No.

21:04.263 --> 21:05.962
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

21:06.031 --> 21:08.398
- Awesome.

21:08.467 --> 21:11.034
<i>[all moaning and grunting]</i>

21:11.103 --> 21:13.203
<i>Never mind on the breakup,</i>
<i>right?</i>

21:13.272 --> 21:17.207
<i>- ♪ Baby, baby, baby ♪</i>

21:17.276 --> 21:20.210
<i>♪ I can't take it anymore ♪</i>

21:20.279 --> 21:22.145
<i>- Yes, more. More.</i>
<i>Good, good, good, good, good.</i>

21:22.214 --> 21:23.747
<i>Come on back.</i>
<i>- Back, back, back, back.</i>

21:23.816 --> 21:25.148
<i>both: Back, back, back,</i>
<i>back, back.</i>

21:25.217 --> 21:26.516
<i>- So you're about this far.</i>

21:26.585 --> 21:27.718
<i>- You see that?</i>
<i>- Right here.</i>

21:27.787 --> 21:28.986
<i>- It's two people.</i>

21:29.055 --> 21:31.389
<i>You have plenty of room.</i>
